28:04.080 --> 28:05.940
You're a good writer, Nick.

28:07.480 --> 28:10.930
I give this writing... an A-plus.

28:11.950 --> 28:14.680
You just tell us
what we need to know,

28:14.740 --> 28:18.580
and you two kids, you get to go
live happily-ever-after.

28:18.640 --> 28:22.290
You give me
little nieces and nephews.

28:22.360 --> 28:27.160
- Listen to me, man. I never worked at a casino.
- No, Nick.

28:27.220 --> 28:31.510
That guy who wrote that letter ?
That's Nick Cassidy.

28:31.580 --> 28:33.560
I was in the joint with him.

28:33.620 --> 28:35.510
He rode a two-year
manslaughter bit...

28:35.570 --> 28:38.640
for killing some guy who was bothering
his girlfriend in a bar.

28:38.710 --> 28:43.290
He's dead. He wrote those letters.
He worked at a casino.

28:43.350 --> 28:47.290
Me ? My last job
was at a Quick Lube.

28:47.350 --> 28:51.580
I did five for lifting cars. That's it.
He was my cellmate. That's how l know him.

28:51.640 --> 28:53.950
I'm sorry about your sister.

28:54.010 --> 28:56.350
I just got out of the joint.

28:56.410 --> 28:58.940
I just wanna...

28:59.000 --> 29:01.690
I don't know anything. I don't
remember anybody. I just wanna go home.

29:11.450 --> 29:13.880
- Bur this guy.
- No. Gabriel, no. - What ?

29:13.950 --> 29:17.790
- Gabriel, you promised.
- I promised that when he helped us, we'd be gone.

29:17.860 --> 29:19.930
When he helped us.
This guy doesn't wanna play.

29:20.060 --> 29:21.750
No, you promised me!

29:21.850 --> 29:24.800
And you promised me
you'd get your sweetheart to help !

29:26.980 --> 29:30.940
He'd rather die... than be with you.

29:32.550 --> 29:34.750
He'd make a fucked-up
boyfriend anyway.

29:37.250 --> 29:39.320
Bur this guy
all over the place.

29:39.420 --> 29:42.460
No. No ! Gabriel, no !

29:42.560 --> 29:44.960
Shut up !

30:01.440 --> 30:03.330
Don't get no blood
on my shoes.

30:05.340 --> 30:09.470
All right, all right. What do you want to know ?
About the casino, the Tomahawk ?

30:09.570 --> 30:12.740
Jesus Christ,
what do you wanna know ?

30:22.470 --> 30:26.630
Six months writing love letters,
my pen pal fucks me over.

30:26.720 --> 30:29.480
Thanks for the stamps, Ash.

30:29.580 --> 30:31.690
All right.
What do you wanna know ?

30:31.780 --> 30:34.240
Everthing.

30:34.340 --> 30:36.490
Nick, I love you, baby.

30:36.590 --> 30:40.290
- Nick, I love you.
- Hey !

30:40.390 --> 30:43.400
She said she loves you.
Say something.

30:44.460 --> 30:46.630
I had better sex in prison.

30:49.290 --> 30:51.520
Throw him back in the rig.

30:53.220 --> 30:55.430
Monster, he's not the guy.

30:57.570 --> 31:01.320
Whole time you were drivin',
he was tellin' her he's not the guy.

31:01.410 --> 31:05.640
He's not the guy. I understand
why he'd tell us he's not the guy,

31:05.730 --> 31:09.260
but why would he tell her
that he's not the guy ?

31:09.350 --> 31:12.650
Maybe...
Maybe he's not the guy.

31:33.070 --> 31:36.210
Look, if I went in the joint with a library card,
I'd come out with a librar card.

31:40.750 --> 31:45.960
The man who wrote those letters
loved Ashley, boys.

31:46.060 --> 31:48.690
He lived for her.

31:53.200 --> 31:55.030
Where's she work ?

31:55.120 --> 31:57.000
What ?

31:57.100 --> 32:00.080
Wrote you a hundred letters,
didn't she ? Where's she work ?

32:00.170 --> 32:02.000
Lindstrom's, beauty and fragrances.

32:02.090 --> 32:05.140
What's her middle name ?

32:05.230 --> 32:06.870
Samantha.

32:12.720 --> 32:14.860
What'd they call her
in high school ?

32:16.470 --> 32:18.650
- What'd they call her in college ?
- What college ?

32:18.740 --> 32:21.330
- What's her greatest fear ?
- Brother.

32:21.430 --> 32:25.620
Oh, wrong. It's drowning.

32:25.710 --> 32:28.660
Wrong, it's her brother.

32:34.710 --> 32:36.530
That's love.

32:39.630 --> 32:42.990
It's time to start talking,

32:43.090 --> 32:45.150
Nick.

32:46.200 --> 32:49.660
Time to start tellin' tales.

32:51.640 --> 32:55.930
- Get him up here.
- No, no, no ! Fuck that !

32:56.020 --> 32:58.780
Nick doesn't do anything
till Nick gets something for Nick.

32:58.870 --> 33:01.470
Ya got it ?
I want some hot chocolate.

33:03.390 --> 33:05.210
You wanna hear
about some job of mine ?

33:05.310 --> 33:08.570
I wanna see some goddamn
hot chocolate...

33:08.670 --> 33:10.910
and some pecan fuckin' pie !

33:11.100 --> 33:14.810
Sure nice pie.

33:19.770 --> 33:21.820
So, when you worked there...

33:29.690 --> 33:31.520
You knew the place...

33:43.170 --> 33:46.430
Okay.

33:46.530 --> 33:50.390
You know what ? I could really go
for some onion rings.

33:50.490 --> 33:52.640
You said talk.
That's all you s...

33:52.740 --> 33:55.810
Gabriel, you said
you wanted to talk.

34:01.410 --> 34:03.620
- How much money is in that casino ?
- Hard to say.

34:03.680 --> 34:06.280
Well, take a guess.

34:08.830 --> 34:10.429
Five million ?

34:10.530 --> 34:14.300
- Jesus. Come here.
- You, you wrote Ash a letter with a stor...

34:14.400 --> 34:17.540
about working Christmas Eve.

34:17.630 --> 34:20.580
About how they send half the security
guys home. Nobody's comin' in and out.

34:20.679 --> 34:22.820
And the rest of ya
are gettin' shit-faced.

34:22.889 --> 34:25.030
That a true story or not ?

34:25.120 --> 34:27.460
Christmas Eve.

34:27.550 --> 34:31.199
We're takin' down that casino,
convict.

34:31.270 --> 34:35.270
And you're the guy
that's gonna tell us how.

34:38.659 --> 34:40.800
That's what we can see.

34:40.870 --> 34:44.900
Now, you tell us what we can't see.
Where the private doors go,

34:44.969 --> 34:48.260
where the alarms are,
what the upstairs looks like, all of it.

34:48.360 --> 34:51.550
- That's not the Tomahawk.
- What the hell are you talkin' about ?

34:51.650 --> 34:55.850
What's this, the cage ?
I mean, the cage is over here.

34:55.940 --> 34:57.770
Ya got...
This whole thing's mixed up.

34:57.860 --> 34:59.780
- That's what it looks like, Romeo.
- Since when ?

34:59.880 --> 35:01.670
I mean, what's this ?

35:01.770 --> 35:05.640
- That's the prime rib buffet. $ 5.99.
- Buffet ?

35:05.740 --> 35:08.710
Buffet is over here
by the bar.

35:08.810 --> 35:11.690
They must've remodeled
the place.

35:11.760 --> 35:14.020
- What ?
- Big guy, the boss.

35:14.120 --> 35:18.480
- The guy that ran the place, was in charge.
- Jack Bangs.

35:18.570 --> 35:22.250
Jack Bangs ! Was always talkin'
about giving the place a makeover.

35:22.320 --> 35:24.490
Must've gone ahead and done that
while I was in the Mountain.

35:24.580 --> 35:27.340
I mean, this thing's
all changed around.

35:27.430 --> 35:30.090
I can't help you with this. I don't
know where security or anything is.

35:30.190 --> 35:35.140
- I have no idea.
- Look, I don't care about the pancake breakfast. I...

35:35.240 --> 35:37.060
You wanna know about money,
right ?

35:37.160 --> 35:41.330
Okay. Where you got the buffet down here ?
That used to be Bang's office.

35:41.420 --> 35:44.270
And he kept a safe in there.

35:44.360 --> 35:48.870
And that safe had all the money
that he was skimming in there.

35:48.940 --> 35:52.780
- And it was called the pow-wow safe.
- Pow-wow safe ?

35:52.910 --> 35:55.760
Yes, pow-wow safe.

35:55.820 --> 35:58.610
'Cause he was stealing money
from the tribe.

35:58.670 --> 36:01.330
The guy had thousands in there.
Millions probably.

36:01.420 --> 36:05.740
Millions ?
In the pow-wow safe ?

36:05.840 --> 36:08.210
Millions.

36:08.310 --> 36:12.400
But, I mean, you know,

36:12.490 --> 36:15.850
it's just that now you
tell me his office is moved.

36:15.950 --> 36:18.320
God knows what else is different.
You know ?

36:18.390 --> 36:20.270
The security, the...

36:20.340 --> 36:24.400
You want me to show you
what goes where, l have no idea!

36:25.550 --> 36:29.620
Well, I guess
we don't need you then.

36:35.600 --> 36:39.920
Well, not necessarily.

36:40.020 --> 36:45.420
Because, if you get me inside,
then I know where the money moves.

36:45.520 --> 36:48.370
I know the security routines.
I know their signals to each other.

36:48.440 --> 36:51.280
I know how they operate.
You get me in there,

36:51.350 --> 36:55.260
then I can work with this map,
and I can tell you if anything's changed.

36:55.350 --> 36:57.490
Wrong, convict.

36:57.590 --> 36:59.990
You walk in there,
they recognize you.

37:00.090 --> 37:02.230
So what ?

37:02.320 --> 37:05.150
If they recognize him, they'll
remember him when the job goes down.

37:05.200 --> 37:07.770
- They won't recognize me. Trust me.
- Why not ?

37:09.300 --> 37:13.170
'Cause you're gonna get me
a disguise.

37:13.400 --> 37:16.440
What happened to working together?

37:16.530 --> 37:20.850
- Your at herbeback in the Mountain ?
- Might as well be.

37:20.950 --> 37:25.020
Don't get 50 channels
in the Mountain. Sleep well.

37:25.120 --> 37:28.250
Tomorrow you got singin'
for your supper to do.

37:32.350 --> 37:34.750
Help yourself.

37:34.840 --> 37:37.720
Sure, take that.
I don't need it.

37:50.400 --> 37:53.280
Nick. Nick.

37:53.370 --> 37:55.290
Let me help you.

37:55.390 --> 37:58.270
- Get your own room, Ashley. Get your own room.
- Let me help you.

37:58.370 --> 38:00.700
He said when you come out,
he wants to talk to you. That's all !

38:00.770 --> 38:02.970
I thought he meant after
New Years, back in Detroit.

38:03.070 --> 38:06.240
- But you knew what he wanted. Right ?
- I thought we had more days.

38:06.330 --> 38:08.900
For what ? What are you gonna do ?
Talk me into helping ?

38:08.990 --> 38:11.360
You know how I feel about my brother !
You know how I hate him.

38:11.450 --> 38:15.710
What did you think's gonna happen ?
This thing's gonna be over and he's gonna let me go ?

38:15.810 --> 38:18.430
He's gonna shoot me
in the back of the head like this !

38:18.530 --> 38:22.010
Or I'm back in prison for the rest
of my life, and that's it for me !

38:22.110 --> 38:25.600
This is my life too, you know.
You think he's just gonna let me walk ?

38:25.700 --> 38:29.120
You think he's not gonna
take this out on me ?

38:29.210 --> 38:32.070
I'm in this too,
and I'm really scared.

38:32.130 --> 38:38.560
Please ! Nick.

38:40.610 --> 38:45.030
Do you remember all
those letters you wrote me ?

38:45.120 --> 38:48.510
About me and you
against the whole world ?

38:53.640 --> 38:55.490
God !

38:55.560 --> 38:59.810
You know, it's just my luck.

38:59.880 --> 39:04.350
I finally meet a boy that I'm crazy about,
and my brother wants him worse than I do.

39:04.450 --> 39:06.270
Why didn't you tell me
your brother was a criminal ?

39:06.340 --> 39:10.310
Gabriel knows some guys
in Miami and New York.

39:10.400 --> 39:13.030
Guys that he helps
get guns to Detroit.

39:13.130 --> 39:16.010
- That's it. That's all I know.
- And that's who he's working for on this one ?

39:16.110 --> 39:18.950
No. He doesn't
wanna work for anyone.

39:19.040 --> 39:22.120
- What's the last place they took down ?
- What ?

39:22.210 --> 39:25.670
Monster and his merry men.
What's the last place they robbed ?

39:25.760 --> 39:27.690
Who they ripped off ?
What did they do ?

39:30.410 --> 39:34.640
I don't think they've robbed anywhere
before. They just... They drive guns !

39:35.690 --> 39:37.860
They've never done a robber ?

39:42.370 --> 39:44.430
Really ?

39:44.530 --> 39:47.020
They really do need me.

39:47.120 --> 39:50.190
They actually need me.

39:58.410 --> 40:01.290
A cowboy.

40:01.390 --> 40:06.640
You're sending me into an lndian casino
dressed like a cowboy.

40:06.730 --> 40:09.200
- Thought this through entirely ?
- It was that or a ballerina.

40:09.300 --> 40:14.250
Well, I mean, I'm gonna need
some money. It is a casino.

40:18.930 --> 40:22.740
- Ten bucks ? What am I gonna do with ten bucks ?
- Don't tip.

40:22.830 --> 40:25.100
Look, if we're
gonna be workin' together,

40:25.200 --> 40:27.920
you shouldn't send me in there like the
Lone Ranger with ten bucks to throw down.

40:28.020 --> 40:32.720
You want me to not get noticed. Not
gettin' noticed costs at least a couple hundred.

40:32.780 --> 40:35.470
Ante up, boys.

41:08.980 --> 41:10.840
Don't lose.

41:10.900 --> 41:15.290
Yeah. Do I get, like, a countr-western
name, or are we just gonna...

41:15.380 --> 41:19.440
You get recognized, you get
a countr-western funeral !

41:19.540 --> 41:21.880
Come on. Come on.

41:21.940 --> 41:24.670
Get your hands off me !

41:26.590 --> 41:29.470
Are you ready
to go gamblin', darlin' ?

41:29.560 --> 41:33.080
Here. She is now.

41:33.170 --> 41:36.500
All right. You all keep an eye
on my guitar now.

41:45.020 --> 41:46.900
Jumpy.

41:53.880 --> 41:57.020
Nick, you're making it
really hard to apologize.

41:57.080 --> 41:59.520
Is that what you're trin' to do ?
Say it with car keys.

41:59.580 --> 42:02.400
Nick, a lot of relationships start out
like this, you know, family problems ?

42:02.460 --> 42:05.210
Save it, Bam-Bam.

42:07.010 --> 42:09.560
You wanna know the problem
with the Tomahawk Casino ?

42:09.630 --> 42:13.630
You wanna know the one thing
holding us back from greatness ?

42:13.690 --> 42:17.720
Snow. S-N-O-fucking-W.
Snow.

42:17.790 --> 42:20.990
There is no snow in Las Vegas, okay ?

42:21.050 --> 42:23.000
They don't want it.
They don't need it.

42:23.070 --> 42:25.790
As a matter of fact,
I think they have laws against the shit.

42:25.850 --> 42:31.450
You guys hired me because you wanted
Las Vegas quality. I brought it to you.

42:31.520 --> 42:34.780
You wanted Las Vegas press.
I gave that to you.

42:34.850 --> 42:37.350
But I cannot give you
Las Vegas profits...

42:37.400 --> 42:40.670
until you people get together
around a campfire, smoke a pipe,

42:40.740 --> 42:44.510
and do some kind of spirit dance
about this goddamn snow !

42:44.580 --> 42:48.130
They did a lot of work. This restaurant
here is the main expansion.

42:48.200 --> 42:51.110
And, they moved the games around.

42:57.860 --> 43:00.130
Do you know that guy ?

43:00.200 --> 43:03.300
Yeah, that's... that's Mike.

43:03.370 --> 43:06.980
Mike. He works here.

43:07.040 --> 43:10.310
Spend some of your brother's money.
I'm gonna go look around.

43:11.910 --> 43:14.850
I was just thinkin', maybe you fellas
would like to stick around,

43:14.920 --> 43:18.820
try the $ 5.99 prime rib.

43:32.230 --> 43:34.440
A couple of rum and cokes, please.

43:34.500 --> 43:38.120
Barry, gimme a bottle
of any goddamn thing ya got. Hurry up.

43:38.180 --> 43:41.990
Cheap two dollar fuckin' bettors.

43:42.060 --> 43:46.730
Hey, how ya doin', cowboy ?
How are ya ?

43:46.790 --> 43:49.130
- Great.
- Jack Bangs is the name. I run the place.

43:51.530 --> 43:53.450
Let me ask you something.

43:53.510 --> 43:57.000
How'd you hear about us ?
Radio ? TV ? Cable ?

43:57.070 --> 44:00.740
Prison. Prison.

44:06.000 --> 44:08.590
I can't go back to Vegas.

44:19.340 --> 44:21.520
We won! We won!

44:23.020 --> 44:25.580
What the hell
was that all about ?

44:25.650 --> 44:28.460
Nothing, man. He just wanted to know
how I heard about the place.

44:28.530 --> 44:31.340
Just fuckin' tone down a little bit,
all right ? Ease up off me.

44:32.620 --> 44:34.890
Oh, my God !
I'm sorry.

44:34.960 --> 44:36.810
Jesus Christ.

44:36.880 --> 44:38.860
I'm sorry. Here, hold this.

44:38.930 --> 44:40.780
What are you doing ?

44:40.850 --> 44:45.070
Security's not all that changed.
Let me go clean this up.

44:45.140 --> 44:48.080
- What was that ?
- His face fell off. Take this.

45:06.650 --> 45:08.760
Hey, a hundred bucks
to wear this jacket.

45:08.820 --> 45:11.790
- Jesus, don't kill me !
- Relax, kid, nobody's gonna kill you.

45:11.860 --> 45:13.850
Santa's gonna give you a hundred bucks
and a wild west jacket.

45:16.880 --> 45:20.720
Hey, baby.
Gimme one of those.

45:24.920 --> 45:27.580
- How're you ?
- Fuckin' freezing.

45:29.720 --> 45:31.760
How long you work here ?

45:31.830 --> 45:34.130
Five years, since it opened.

45:34.200 --> 45:37.010
- How long since your makeover ?
- My what ?

45:37.080 --> 45:40.600
I'm talkin' about the place. The
remodeling, moving everthing around.

45:40.660 --> 45:45.200
The Tomahawk's been the same ever since I started,
buddy. It's the losers that change.

45:47.740 --> 45:50.070
Lyin' motherfucker !

45:53.310 --> 45:55.160
Go, kid, go !

46:01.950 --> 46:03.800
Hey !

46:05.120 --> 46:06.680
Shit !

46:27.350 --> 46:31.960
- It's your jacket, you can have it !
He gave me a hundred bucks. - Shit !

46:39.130 --> 46:42.240
- What the hell happened, man ?
- The man fucked up !

46:42.300 --> 46:45.860
This building is the same from day one !
It hasn't been changed !

46:45.920 --> 46:49.860
Monster, he was talkin' to the manager
inside there. There he is !

46:54.660 --> 46:57.020
Go, go, go, go !

46:57.090 --> 46:59.130
Come on !
Get him back !

47:19.200 --> 47:22.530
Keep on running, Romeo !
Keep on running !

47:22.600 --> 47:25.860
As fast as you go,
we'll get there !

47:25.920 --> 47:29.730
- We're truckers, motherfucker!
We drive for a living !

47:52.780 --> 47:55.720
Help ! Help !

47:55.780 --> 47:58.990
He thinks he's gettin' away.

48:00.770 --> 48:02.920
Oh, shit !

48:18.630 --> 48:21.480
No !

48:36.590 --> 48:38.740
Come on. Come on!

48:54.730 --> 48:57.870
We gotta get to those trees.

49:07.920 --> 49:10.710
Oh, shit !

49:47.290 --> 49:50.900
C'mon ! Get 'em outta there !
C'mon !

49:50.970 --> 49:53.300
- Is she all right ?
- All right, all right !

49:53.370 --> 49:58.140
At the rate you're goin', I'm gonna
have trouble considerin' you family.

49:58.200 --> 50:01.620
Hey, there !
You folks need some help ?

50:06.040 --> 50:09.180
- I say, you need some help ?
- Get outta here, man !

50:09.240 --> 50:12.540
- Shut the fuck up !
- Get the fuck outta here !

50:12.600 --> 50:16.600
Well, if you need
some help...

50:19.220 --> 50:21.090
Gabriel, no!

50:21.140 --> 50:24.980
Gabriel, he won't hurt us.
He won't remember us. Don't do it.

50:25.050 --> 50:26.900
Shut the fuck up !

50:29.210 --> 50:30.690
No !

50:32.990 --> 50:36.190
Oh, God !

50:46.780 --> 50:49.950
What's this ? What's this ?
This isn't the Tomahawk. No.

50:50.010 --> 50:51.870
No, I've never seen this before.

50:51.930 --> 50:54.310
They must have given the place
a makeover. Yeah !

50:54.360 --> 50:58.150
The buffet was over here, the blackjack was over here,
the bar used to be over here.

50:58.200 --> 51:00.190
I don't know. I can't help you.
I have no idea.

51:00.260 --> 51:02.370
I have no idea !

51:02.430 --> 51:05.570
Somethin' tells me you're not
being totally honest with me.

51:05.630 --> 51:07.490
What'd you tell
